contentTypes.name: Landing Page
contentTypes.description: Represents a Landing Page and its metadata. Contains a list of Landing Page Sections

contentTypes.name: Landing Page Section
contentTypes.description: Represents a specific part of a Landing Page, and that section's component type. A Section contains one or more Content blocks (depending on the component) .

contentTypes.name: Link
contentTypes.description: Represents a Link inside a Landing Page Content block.

settings.helpText: Name of the page. Used to generate the slug for the page.
Represents the path to the page, e.g. 'slug-name' creates the page at "https://yourpage.com/slug-name".
Set to true to prevent this page from being indexed by search engines
Used as the page's meta title
Used as the meta description of the page.
Used as the social media image for the page when shared on social media.
The list of sections that will appear on the page
Name of the section. Useful for content editors in Contentful.
Represents the layout of this section.
Represents the heading at the top of the section
Represents the content within the section. Some component types may accept more than one content block.
Name of the Content block. Useful for content editors in Contentful.
Secondary text of context within a section.
Up to two links to be added to the section.
Href field. For internal links, should be relative path (e.g. /path-to-page). For external links, should be an absolute path (e.g. http(s)://my-url.com)
Represents the visible text in the button or link

secondaryText.en-US: This starter uses as few dependencies as possible to create landing pages in Gatsby with Contentful, and it's intended to be quick and easy to incorporate your own styles to match the look and feel of your brand.

The components included in this starter are meant as a starting point to demonstrate using Contentful to build landing pages in Gatsby, which lets you extend the functionality by building your own custom components.
You can customize the colors, typography, and components baked into this starter to match your own visual branding.
